{"title":"Micro. - Identificación de Microorganismos en el Laboratorio-2024","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/Infectología/Micro. - Identificación de Microorganismos en el Laboratorio-2024.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"- Identificación de Microorganismos\\Nen el Laboratorio","guid":"UAVSkmVDmJsHK6uiTBUDSQ","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"A. Técnicas para identificación de\\Nlos agentes infecciosos","guid":"FJi-HFuxJNRXJJ_fBS36BQ","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"1. Observación","guid":"","children":[{"id":"3","parent":"2","text":"• a) Macroscópica:","guid":"NnTDmhPPNXMA9LFgAlSCGA","children":[{"id":"4","parent":"3","text":"• Identificación de parásitos visibles a simple vista (ej. : Pediculus corporis, Phthirus pubis).","guid":"afsY9yf1G9dkkpGGOgBriQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"5","parent":"2","text":"• b) Microscópica:","guid":"R29h_V06DrIm_2yUX60Rog","children":[{"id":"6","parent":"5","text":"• b.1) Microscopía directa al fresco: Observación sin tinción.","guid":"fooOsySUa_t8XdkeRYCdvA","children":[]},{"id":"7","parent":"5","text":"• b.2) Microscopía con tinciones: Uso de colorantes específicos (e.g., Tinción de Gram).","guid":"c3-lkxmbM9QX1bOaKfRpLQ","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"8","parent":"1","text":"2. Aislamiento y\\NTécnicas de Cultivo","guid":"QL-A0hDbfMxRZe3ITfg1RQ","children":[{"id":"9","parent":"8","text":"• Desarrollo in vitro en medios con factores nutritivos y ambientales.","guid":"ND85EBuqZPlKCeeUTIzPAw","children":[]},{"id":"10","parent":"8","text":"• Propósito: Obtener colonias, caracterización bioquímica y antigénica.","guid":"G7YcAjk-ZtsxYW7rGkAqtQ","children":[]},{"id":"11","parent":"8","text":"• Limitaciones: No todos los microorganismos se pueden cultivar (e.g., M. leprae).","guid":"XdLS1i2_SApfwMhyUVJ4ag","children":[]}]},{"id":"12","parent":"1","text":"3. Detección de Componentes Estructurales o\\NProductos del Agente Infeccioso","guid":"","children":[{"id":"13","parent":"12","text":"• Identificación de antígenos, toxinas, y enzimas sin cultivo.","guid":"EGDhByePzN0MKmdlUSBh2Q","children":[]},{"id":"14","parent":"12","text":"• Técnicas principales:","guid":"JatTWxzETSR8OB0GWeqMbA","children":[{"id":"15","parent":"14","text":"• Inmunoensayos: ELISA, Inmunofluorescencia, Radioinmunoanálisis.","guid":"OG6yHUZCBJomd1tvVCTOHw","children":[]},{"id":"16","parent":"14","text":"• Aglutinación: Uso de partículas poliméricas (e.g., látex).","guid":"f4BrdlfYylpuZPjVXVM-TA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"17","parent":"1","text":"4. Detección de\\NÁcidos Nucleicos","guid":"","children":[{"id":"18","parent":"17","text":"• Descripción: Detección de material genético (ADN o ARN) del agente infeccioso en muestras clínicas.","guid":"Rbw9UynsmE5Bt3NpVh0eWg","children":[]},{"id":"19","parent":"17","text":"• Métodos:","guid":"K3Iv-0ZWF1E-7LJyYH3hxA","children":[{"id":"20","parent":"19","text":"• Hibridización: Unión de ADN complementario con sondas genéticas.","guid":"VThWRDf60gJKPv7beuOpnw","children":[]},{"id":"21","parent":"19","text":"• Amplificación: PCR (Reacción en cadena de la polimerasa).","guid":"VL8fJkZ3G-JUzjYLDS3RRA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"22","parent":"1","text":"5. Cito-histopatología","guid":"","children":[{"id":"23","parent":"22","text":"• Citopatología:","guid":"Ux5b1U-3mDhpjMo_WLZuOQ","children":[{"id":"24","parent":"23","text":"• Estudio de células individuales obtenidas de secreciones o biopsias.","guid":"Hd1ZfxgygPUlqPx8Y5mW0w","children":[]},{"id":"25","parent":"23","text":"• Muestras pueden ser extendidas directamente o concentradas por centrifugación.","guid":"Qh8ZQ2dgb-U5trUtE5t-bg","children":[]}]},{"id":"26","parent":"22","text":"• Histopatología:","guid":"NUJKs2D0NWEdgy1CYLR6rw","children":[{"id":"27","parent":"26","text":"• Estudio de tejidos completos obtenidos por procedimientos invasivos (biopsia, autopsia).","guid":"J0pMslxv37RBMlxzfIKi9g","children":[]},{"id":"28","parent":"26","text":"• Observación microscópica de cortes finos del tejido.","guid":"FGqxtgtxW093ZkyWaSnQ3Q","children":[]}]},{"id":"29","parent":"22","text":"• Tinciones\\NEspecializadas:","guid":"Ueh3MUw0gqF2V6IhXqGXrQ","children":[{"id":"30","parent":"29","text":"• Gram y Warthin-Starry: Bacterias.","guid":"J2HZvVRn7d9zTt4qRT8zPA","children":[]},{"id":"31","parent":"29","text":"• Ziehl Neelsen: Mycobacterias.","guid":"bJpu1Bj32qco2MoPLrmIGA","children":[]},{"id":"32","parent":"29","text":"• Gomori-Grocott y PAS: Hongos.","guid":"AFhKjGKPfz1CVQaGNZqVQA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"33","parent":"1","text":"6. Detección de Anticuerpos\\NEspecíficos (Serología)","guid":"Q4O0nl_YM8kWTw_vas4BUA","children":[{"id":"34","parent":"33","text":"• Descripción: Diagnóstico indirecto mediante la detección de anticuerpos específicos en el suero del paciente.","guid":"YvLHsV628N053JYRNNs-4g","children":[]},{"id":"35","parent":"33","text":"• Indicaciones:","guid":"KutzfjA0ODITfNaQcmWHmg","children":[{"id":"36","parent":"35","text":"• Diagnóstico de infección aguda (medición de IgM).","guid":"B955tn5X-jAM_feLL0BTcw","children":[]},{"id":"37","parent":"35","text":"• Seguimiento de la seroconversión (IgG).","guid":"Ur_oDwBM1bZ0f4awP1pW4w","children":[]}]},{"id":"38","parent":"33","text":"• Aplicaciones:","guid":"GUSwXR1YUL9uE977GZz66Q","children":[{"id":"39","parent":"38","text":"• Enfermedades virales (hepatitis, VIH, rubéola, sarampión).","guid":"f-fP_DBo5YJPN5ApQ2uEmg","children":[]},{"id":"40","parent":"38","text":"• Enfermedades parasitarias (toxoplasmosis, Chagas).","guid":"EEEZS2WGoBguOYXrTIksyA","children":[]},{"id":"41","parent":"38","text":"• Enfermedades bacterianas (Mycoplasma pneumoniae, Legionella, Bartonella henselae).","guid":"PQgMexWKKjIdO_H8H_rULA","children":[]}]},{"id":"42","parent":"33","text":"• Técnicas Serológicas:","guid":"dEEbD1cYiA1U1hMPHyyOjQ","children":[{"id":"43","parent":"42","text":"• Inmunofluorescencia\\N(IF):","guid":"TIcJ9n5-V6o1X-yzF4k5Ng","children":[{"id":"44","parent":"43","text":"• IF Directa:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"45","parent":"44","text":"• Detecta antígenos en muestras usando anticuerpos marcados con fluorescencia.","guid":"HtzjaTLrFBl4xSLBOCGTxg","children":[]},{"id":"46","parent":"44","text":"• Se observa la fluorescencia al microscopio, indicando la presencia de antígenos específicos.","guid":"UENk2WbZAb1Rvo6wUCs01Q","children":[]}]},{"id":"47","parent":"43","text":"• IF Indirecta:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"48","parent":"47","text":"• Utiliza un anticuerpo primario para unirse al antígeno en la muestra, seguido de un anticuerpo secundario marcado con fluorescencia.","guid":"F0HnPyD2HtkTlrlwJ4MAig","children":[]},{"id":"49","parent":"47","text":"• El complejo formado emite fluorescencia bajo el microscopio.","guid":"Bny-8kHQP1t0DC1SQ4TLbQ","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"50","parent":"42","text":"• ELISA (Enzyme-Linked\\NImmunosorbent Assay):","guid":"ZJ1bviQ0ljNfIVg8axoasA","children":[{"id":"51","parent":"50","text":"• Procedimiento:","guid":"V1ppjRFIH09jf5-ZS5uEnA","children":[{"id":"52","parent":"51","text":"1. Unión: El antígeno o anticuerpo se adhiere a una placa.","guid":"aGCnXDhVsqhqyBMpb61nnA","children":[]},{"id":"53","parent":"51","text":"2. Lavado: Elimina cualquier material no unido.","guid":"IKicR3xaKVF-2KGSB1OAFg","children":[]},{"id":"54","parent":"51","text":"3. Conjugado: Se añade un anticuerpo marcado con enzima (conjugado) que se une al antígeno o anticuerpo.","guid":"Guo3BT1ELvtAvkv0Occabg","children":[]},{"id":"55","parent":"51","text":"4. Sustrato: Se añade un sustrato que la enzima convierte en un producto detectable (colorimétrico).","guid":"cC9DFTmDbrZx6K41QHKn7g","children":[]}]},{"id":"56","parent":"50","text":"• Resultados: La intensidad del color indica la cantidad de anticuerpo o antígeno presente en la muestra.","guid":"IFxwc0OnPOUQndzDN55Xsg","children":[]}]},{"id":"57","parent":"42","text":"• Western Blot:","guid":"RvaPCU7rOZgdPVq2UlUV3g","children":[{"id":"58","parent":"57","text":"• Descripción: Técnica confirmatoria para la detección de anticuerpos específicos en suero.","guid":"ZgTVjlMthY4unuYdPV8_Gw","children":[]},{"id":"59","parent":"57","text":"• Procedimiento:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"60","parent":"59","text":"1. Separación de Proteínas: Las proteínas del patógeno se separan por peso molecular mediante electroforesis en gel.","guid":"ZHWk3RIehbcI-sO3TNZMOg","children":[]},{"id":"61","parent":"59","text":"2. Transferencia: Las proteínas separadas se transfieren a una membrana (nitrocelulosa o PVDF).","guid":"SnQ4X3PC1uE8g7PWaxzUpw","children":[]},{"id":"62","parent":"59","text":"3. Incubación con Suero: La membrana se incuba con el suero del paciente, permitiendo que los anticuerpos específicos se unan a las proteínas diana.","guid":"cB0AMjtcVWhycFS9Cwc3Nw","children":[]},{"id":"63","parent":"59","text":"4. Lavado: Se eliminan los anticuerpos no específicos.","guid":"eKCEYzMuoLJEzlGmaM_HeA","children":[]},{"id":"64","parent":"59","text":"5. Conjugado: Se añade un anticuerpo secundario conjugado con una enzima, que se une a los anticuerpos del paciente.","guid":"bLIPaDa2_9spQm9mDQ5_2w","children":[]},{"id":"65","parent":"59","text":"6. Sustrato: La enzima convierte el sustrato en un producto visible (coloración o fluorescencia).","guid":"el48wDngTCpErNeNXvuYfg","children":[]}]},{"id":"66","parent":"57","text":"• Resultados: La visualización de bandas en la membrana indica la presencia de anticuerpos específicos del paciente, confirmando la infección.","guid":"XhTiXSPOL8lKFbMvRBm37A","children":[]}]}]}]}]},{"id":"67","parent":"0","text":"B. Principales\\NTinciones Utilizadas","guid":"GD2vpQCHhe92drgTGEclwg","children":[{"id":"68","parent":"67","text":"1. Gram","guid":"","children":[{"id":"69","parent":"68","text":"• Reactivos: Cristal violeta, lugol, acetona, safranina.","guid":"dvu1V3i0mUwBePcHW3FaNQ","children":[]},{"id":"70","parent":"68","text":"• Principio: Gram (+) retienen cristal violeta; Gram (–) se tiñen con safranina (rojo).","guid":"CtMfAwpzur8oR6ZvVUdXYw","children":[]},{"id":"71","parent":"68","text":"• Utilidad: Clasificación bacteriana (Gram +/–).","guid":"fjaRoGTLWkVAZCwKblOR0g","children":[]}]},{"id":"72","parent":"67","text":"2. Tinción de esporas","guid":"","children":[{"id":"73","parent":"72","text":"• Reactivos: Verde de malaquita, safranina.","guid":"ICevrTLUgMd5WskKGMg0EA","children":[]},{"id":"74","parent":"72","text":"• Principio: Tinción de esporas (verde).","guid":"ZgMheT4pGrABl_uJUrUw4Q","children":[]},{"id":"75","parent":"72","text":"• Utilidad: Esporas de Bacilos Gram (+).","guid":"dOAaiyraau9fw7C8bz5XSw","children":[]}]},{"id":"76","parent":"67","text":"3. Kinyoun","guid":"","children":[{"id":"77","parent":"76","text":"• Reactivos: Fucsina, ácido sulfúrico, azul de metileno.","guid":"ZLq3GSRwiElOOe_JQs-Zdw","children":[]},{"id":"78","parent":"76","text":"• Principio: Unión ácida resistente.","guid":"SD64EhhPovgG6VFjPzptag","children":[]},{"id":"79","parent":"76","text":"• Utilidad: Nocardia (BAAR+).","guid":"EQQ8RQhiSGoaq8efG9dbSA","children":[]}]},{"id":"80","parent":"67","text":"4. Naranja de\\Nacridina","guid":"ZFdffXi676ZgrqwQSlqA9g","children":[{"id":"81","parent":"80","text":"• Reactivos: Naranja de acridina (fluorescencia).","guid":"EtYDKULzbg5xHrKrEQyUyQ","children":[]},{"id":"82","parent":"80","text":"• Principio: Tinción del ADN bacteriano.","guid":"J77IUzGC3rV_YCacR-Z4AA","children":[]},{"id":"83","parent":"80","text":"• Utilidad: Bacterias Gram lábiles.","guid":"NuQKVmJGp5kdD7HYK8Qk4Q","children":[]}]},{"id":"84","parent":"67","text":"5. Giménez","guid":"Q_b850No1_kuZ6Z7Vs0AEA","children":[{"id":"85","parent":"84","text":"• Reactivos: Fucsina, verde malaquita.","guid":"DSESiXzTYpQbAnwscdvJog","children":[]},{"id":"86","parent":"84","text":"• Principio: Tinción de la pared bacteriana.","guid":"IUPq3mk8a_U0q2MZaYKi8A","children":[]},{"id":"87","parent":"84","text":"• Utilidad: Bartonella spp., Chlamydia.","guid":"AYwO7juUtHwovRBaEpBLMw","children":[]}]},{"id":"88","parent":"67","text":"6. Ziehl Neelsen","guid":"","children":[{"id":"89","parent":"88","text":"• Reactivos: Fucsina, alcohol-ácido, azul de metileno.","guid":"BlxGBx-GWSdn2ZTaLhsOWg","children":[]},{"id":"90","parent":"88","text":"• Principio: Unión ácido-alcohol resistente.","guid":"UQk33Gc5u3Z2AYZaNWCXWQ","children":[]},{"id":"91","parent":"88","text":"• Utilidad: Mycobacterias (BAAR+), Cryptosporidium.","guid":"X_SrHFawMmt_uxhQFti1cg","children":[]}]},{"id":"92","parent":"67","text":"7. Auramina-rodamina","guid":"","children":[{"id":"93","parent":"92","text":"• Reactivos: Auramina-rodamina, permanganato de potasio.","guid":"OPbaBBzKyihCnNpTRhfsjQ","children":[]},{"id":"94","parent":"92","text":"• Principio: Tinción fluorescente de la pared.","guid":"GZ4svF2fVn8387YwOuIXmg","children":[]},{"id":"95","parent":"92","text":"• Utilidad: Mycobacterias (BAAR+).","guid":"RtvCdGyfGUkkZLqLSGfRYg","children":[]}]},{"id":"96","parent":"67","text":"8. Tinción de cápsula","guid":"","children":[{"id":"97","parent":"96","text":"• Reactivos: Tinta china, safranina.","guid":"KDPNxk0hyuVa-ByVbCrKrQ","children":[]},{"id":"98","parent":"96","text":"• Principio: Contraste de la pared (tinta negra).","guid":"EIqi3wlfwxFC98q9Fubo5g","children":[]},{"id":"99","parent":"96","text":"• Utilidad: Cryptococcus.","guid":"KOYcOCrRX5dFAfdBee9UFA","children":[]}]},{"id":"100","parent":"67","text":"9. Blanco de calcoflúor","guid":"","children":[{"id":"101","parent":"100","text":"• Reactivos: Blanco de calcoflúor, azul de Evans (fluorescencia).","guid":"EgsbDTsDfZsvT-tucf_GKQ","children":[]},{"id":"102","parent":"100","text":"• Principio: Tinción específica para hongos.","guid":"EbOwBi8LA74I2HubSqqKCw","children":[]},{"id":"103","parent":"100","text":"• Utilidad: Hongos filamentosos y levaduras.","guid":"S9XN5kt1Ve4QwnaYZXP6og","children":[]}]},{"id":"104","parent":"67","text":"10. Azul de metileno","guid":"","children":[{"id":"105","parent":"104","text":"• Reactivos: Azul de metileno.","guid":"KRSsbUi2LMggVhI9b_Bu4g","children":[]},{"id":"106","parent":"104","text":"• Principio: Tinción de la pared celular.","guid":"NVVGEkS6zMg4WEBEXYkT2A","children":[]},{"id":"107","parent":"104","text":"• Utilidad: Enteroparásitos, hongos.","guid":"EdyXrRNQXNpJs96FImc6jA","children":[]}]},{"id":"108","parent":"67","text":"11. Giemsa","guid":"","children":[{"id":"109","parent":"108","text":"• Reactivos: Eosina, buffer, azul de metileno, varios azules.","guid":"HLAf6wyrqUI5TiNzRZY8Iw","children":[]},{"id":"110","parent":"108","text":"• Principio: Tinción del núcleo de Plasmodium.","guid":"N30I2n5QGrQ_hZA3SYgj5w","children":[]},{"id":"111","parent":"108","text":"• Utilidad: Plasmodium.","guid":"OVOYT27Ve6U7h-oRSwdIVg","children":[]}]}]}]},"node_count":111,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"Infectología","folder":"Entidades clínicas/Infectología","filename":"Micro. - Identificación de Microorganismos en el Laboratorio-2024","id":"map_1161","resolved_references":[]}